laboratory_examinations.findings: MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA ( >= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.

Gallstones seen within the gallbladder. Circumferential gallbladder wall thickening and edema. Superimposed adenomyomatosis. Echogenic nodule external to the gallbladder neck measuring 1.0 x 0.9 x 1.1 cm.
